By Hellraiser83 on Wednesday, December 5, 2001 - 06:09 am:

I noticed while entering passwords that if you change just the first letter of a password you know gets a certain sub it will still get that sub but not the same main

for some examples, try:

#ablet for sub zan
#oopoo for sub antlan
#ark_art for sub joker
#ark for sub joker with worse stats then previously mentioned

note: # is to represent whatever letter/number/symbol you put before the rest.

He is telling you to put a character in front of oopoo, like aoopoo. That's what the #'s mean up there. Hellraiser is correct, any character tacked onto the front of oopoo, like aoopoo makes a monster whose sub-breed (not main type) is Antlan.
